  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SME Business Lead - MariBank",
  "description": "<p><p><strong>Job Description: </strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead the overall business vision, strategy, and product roadmap for the MariBank SME segment, covering lending, deposits, and embedded financial solutions.</p></li><li><p>Drive SME portfolio growth and client acquisition through technology-enabled, data-led, and partnership-driven solutions.</p></li><li><p>Own SME business P&L and portfolio performance, including balance sheet growth, asset quality, portfolio monitoring, and regular performance reviews.</p></li><li><p>Oversee end-to-end SME product development, from customer journey design and requirement prioritisation to delivery governance and post-launch optimisation.</p></li><li><p>Ensure full compliance with regulatory, credit risk, CDD/KYC, and risk appetite requirements across all SME lending and financing activities.</p></li><li><p>Lead execution of the SME lending strategy, including portfolio scaling, revenue expansion, risk-calibrated lending programs, and new product commercialization.</p></li><li><p>Originate, structure, and approve SME credit solutions, including proposal development, financial analysis, and collaboration with risk and credit stakeholders.</p></li><li><p>Build, lead, and mentor the SME lending and product team, while partnering closely with internal functions and external ecosystem partners to deliver scalable SME solutions.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirement: </strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree or above in any field </p></li><li><p>Minimum 15 years of full-time working experience in business within the bank or financial institution</p></li><li><p>Minimum 10 years of full-time working experience in relevant SME business within the bank or financial institution</p></li><li><p>Prior experience driving digital experience improvements through technology and UI/UX enhancements is strongly preferred</p></li><li><p>Solid understanding of regulatory, compliance, and credit risk requirements relevant to SME lending</p></li><li><p>Ability to work cross-functionally with risk, legal, compliance, treasury, and operations teams</p></li></ul></p>",
